---
title: Neapolitan Aglio E Olio Chicken & Pasta with Garlicolio, Tomato & Parsley
description: Spaghetti aglio e olio translates to “spaghetti with garlic and oil”—and that just about sums it up! This traditional dish from Naples turns a few classic ingredients into something spectacular. Fresh tomato, parsley, and chili flakes shine in a simple garlic-olive oil sauce that clings to pasta. Herbed chicken is served over the top for a meal that proves less really is more!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/6655f7688a4eed4f27b52fdc-178f5a9d.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/6655f7688a4eed4f27b52fdc-en-US.pdf
time required: 25 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 770 kcal
  fat: 37 g
  saturated fat: 8 g
  carbohydrates: 65 g
  sugar: 4 g
  protein: 43 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 260 mg
servings: 2
author: Sara Heilman
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/neapolitan-aglio-e-olio-chicken-and-pasta-6655f7688a4eed4f27b52fdc
course: main course
cuisine: Southern Europe
---

Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Finely dice @tomato{1%unit}. Pick @parsley{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; roughly
chop leaves.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with
half the @Italian seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat.
Add chicken and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{3-5%minutes} per side.

> TIP: If chicken starts to brown too quickly, reduce heat to medium and cover pan after flipping.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} and tent with #foil{} to keep
warm. Wipe out pan and let cool slightly.

Once water is boiling, add @Colavita spaghetti{6%ounce} to pot. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}.

Reserve 1/2 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

Meanwhile, heat @Colavita extra virgin olive oil{5%teaspoon} in pan used for
chicken over medium-low heat. Add tomato and @chili flakes{1%teaspoon};
cook, stirring occasionally, until softened and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

> We used 1/2 tsp chili flakes; add a pinch more if you like things spicy.

Stir in 1/4 cup reserved pasta cooking water. Bring to a simmer, then remove
from heat.

> TIP: If pasta is still cooking, carefully add water directly from pot.

Add drained spaghetti, @butter{1%tablespoon}, and @olive oil{5%teaspoon} to
pan with sauce; toss until evenly coated. Taste and season with @salt{} and
@pepper{} if desired.

Thinly slice chicken crosswise.

Divide pasta between #bowls{} and garnish with parsley. Top with chicken and a
large drizzle of olive oil. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.